BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:sgUe4D8Yicb-I3omMO19u
SUMMARY:Anila Quayyum Agha: Geometry of Light
DTSTAMP:20260321T020259Z
DTSTART:20260401T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Anila Quayyum Agha: Geometry of Light invites you to become par
	t of the art. Agha\, a Pakistani American artist\, animates spaces with he
	r large-scale sculptural installations. Suspended from the ceiling\, Agha’
	s steel cubes are laser-cut with intricate designs that project geometric 
	shadows onto the visitor. She draws on both the light and dark of her own 
	life\, using South Asian art practices to convey the gender discrimination
	 she faced growing up as a young girl in Pakistan. An in-depth exploration
	 of Islamic architecture\, art\, and identity\, this is the first solo exh
	ibition of a Pakistani American artist in SAM’s 90-year history. Agha is c
	arving a name out for herself in the art world—visit the Seattle Asian Art
	 Museum for an immersive and illuminating experience.\n\nhttps://seatoday.
	6amcity.com/events/#/details/anila-quayyum-agha-geometry-of-light/16795597
	/2026-04-01T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
